  "recipeIngredient": [
    "4 large chipping potatoes, such as Yukon Gold,",
    "Spunta or Mans Piper, peeled",
    "vegetable or corn oil for deep-trying",
    "10 garlic cloves, peeled and thinly sliced",
    "sea salt"
  ],
  "recipeInstructions": [
    "sharp knife, cut the potatoes into long matchsticks.",
    "about 3mm thick. Wash them well in a couple of changes of cold water to remove excess starch, then drain and pat dry on a clean tea towel.",
    "Heat an 8cm depth of oil 1n a deep-fat fryer or other suitable deep, heavy pan to 120 l 40\"C. Blanch the matchstick potatoes in manageable batches (a couple of handfuls at a time) for 2-3 minutes, then remove with a slotted spoon and drain 1n a colander.",
    "Increase the temperature of the oil to l 60-180\u00b0C and re-fry the potatoes with the garlic slices in batches, moving them around in the pan, until golden and crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on kitchen paper. Sprinkle with sea salt and serve immediately.",
    "Alternatively, you can keep the straw potatoes warm, uncovered, on a baking tray in a low oven until ready to serve. They should stay crisp but if not you can briefly re-fry them in hot oil to crisp them up again."
  ],
